text.tspan: Blocks aligned on 280x280 grid for easy copy paste
Checkerboard pattern filling, with a one line path.
Create cells that can open and close as pixels.
Now, any picture can be created as a checkerboard pattern line
Blocks ready for use: for the inside pattern, set grid to 280 pixels
to easy copy paste them.
For the outside boarder, set grid to 10px to align.
To recreate a one line path from the blocks:
- copy paste relevant blocks from the template into a pixel pattern.
(make sure edge blocks and inner blocks are correct)
- make sure the blocks are aligned well!
For easy positioning: copy an aligned block,
hover with arrow in grid space where you want block, paste.
(set grid to lines for easy visuals, 280x280 pixels)
- select all blocks
- ungroup
- select all segments
- set to node selection(shortcut: N)
- select all nodes (just field selected all)
- click the icon "two disconnected nodes to one node"
- this can take a while..., one path will be created.
- fill path. Fill rule: "evenodd" (as opposed to non zero)
